OL,3,CWhy do voters give no credit to Sunak
OL,4,Cfor cutting taxes?
OL,6,FRishi Sunak wants to make the election
OL,7,Fabout tax, or more precisely that the
OL,8,FTories would cut taxes and Labour
OL,9,Fwould raise them.
OL,11,FThere are a number of challenges for
OL,12,Fhim with this approach, the most
OL,13,Fobvious one being that the Tories in
OL,14,Fgovernment have raised the burden of -
OL,15,Fthe share of national income taken by
OL,16,Fthe Treasury in taxes - to its highest
OL,17,Flevel since the early 1960s.
OL,19,FIn that sense, he and the have a
OL,20,Fcredibility problem.
