OL,3,CWhy do voters give no credit to Sunak
OL,4,Cfor cutting taxes?
OL,6,FThere are a few reasons. First, anyone
OL,7,Fearning less than #32,000 or more than
OL,8,F#55,000 has been a loser. They may not
OL,9,Fbe the average taxpayer but they are
OL,10,Fthe majority (by the way, those on
OL,11,Fhighest earnings and businesses are
OL,12,Fpaying a lot more tax, and the tax
OL,13,Ftake from VAT has risen considerably).
OL,15,FSecond, and as the IFS also points
OL,16,Fout, the proportion of retired people
OL,17,Fpaying tax is now higher than for
OL,18,Fworking people. This reflects the
OL,19,Fgrowth in the earnings of those over
OL,20,F65.
